https://prismic.io/blog/api-response-times

Factors that affect API response time
1.Server processing time
2.Network latency
3.Third-party dependencies

How to improve API performance

1.Use caching to speed up responses
2.Compress responses to reduce transfer time
3.Optimize database queries
4.Code optimization
5.Use asynchronous processing for long-running requests
6.Implement load balancing to distribute requests
7.Use a content delivery network (CDN)

Best practices for monitoring and troubleshooting API performance
1.Establish key performance indicators (KPIs)
2.Utilize monitoring tools and techniques
3.Analyze API logs
4.Monitor performance at different stages of development

